args:
After the siblings eke out a narrow victory,
they swear to carry on the real Alberius's will
and surpass the ideals he held by continuing
to fight united as one.
That is the core. We are finally at the end.
If this is what my descendants are\ncapable of...then I've nothing to fear...
Maybe stop underestimating us now that\nwe just beat you like a moldy carpet!
Hold, Emile. I felt the black mana leave\nhis body a moment ago—he has cause\nto fight us no longer.
He is free of its corruption now.\nThis is the true Alberius.
Forgive me, my kin. Ah, but I have\nforced so much upon you...
Would that I could have ended it myself...\nBut alas, I was not able.
You were all of you amazing, and I am\ncertain that together you will reach the\nfuture I was unable to see myself.
You are not alone—you needn't become\nlike I was. But I believe you have come\nto realize this already.
Indeed, I seek to be you no longer.\nGreat as they are, your footsteps cannot\nlead me where I must go.
If we are to carry on your will, we must\nforge our own path—one which leads\nbeyond even the ideal you pursued.
Then I leave the rest to you...
Hmph. As if we need to be told.

Well, I'M just glad it's finally over!
And next time some long-dead relative
returns to wreck havoc on the world,
just count me out.
Oh, but the battle to thwart the Progenitor\nwill be far worse than this.
If this mere skirmish has you bellyaching,\nI dread to think of the future.
It sounds like someone needs rather\nintensive training before that day.
H-hey! I'm the emperor of Dyrenell now!\nNobody bosses me around—not even you!
Then I suppose I'd best snatch that throne\nout from under you.
I think that's enough teasing for one day.\nI'm starting to feel sorry for the poor thing.
The empire has begun to settle down under\nyour rule, Emile. Changing leadership now\nwould only sow the seeds of unrest.
The rest of us effectively abandoned\nDyrenell and its people, but you are\ndoing a fine job in our stead.
The empire has only held together as well\nas it has because someone of quality\nsits the throne.
If not for you, Emile, we siblings would\nlikely have been branded cowards who\nabandoned our kingdom and fled.
We all owe you gratitude for that.\nSo...thank you.
So all of you...are thanking me?\nI'd say this is a dream, but even my\ndreams are never this unrealistic...
Explain this madness! You're all fakes like\nthat Alberius, aren't you?! Well, I won't be\ndeceived! YOU WON'T TAKE ME ALIVE!
Stop making a scene, fool. They're merely\nsaying we owe you, so we're suspending\nour final judgment—for now.
But know that unrest across the border\nis a threat to our own stability here.
I'll beat into you precisely what is required\nof a leader to ensure that does not happen.\nPrepare yourself for a thorough lesson.
Ugh, why does it ALWAYS end like this...?
It's all right, Emile. With all of us working\ntogether, we'll overcome any obstacle\nthat stands in our way.
Yes, I suppose if we all work togeth...\nWait, no! Why should I be made to suffer\nall the lessons and beatings and work?!
I'll gladly join you in training; I've always\nfound group sessions more productive.
(If it is to be all of us, I shall also have\nto do my part from now on.)
Then let us be off, each on a path forged\nby our own convictions that leads to a\nshared future of new possibility!
